\section[]{CIDA VARIABILITY SURVEY}

\subsection{Description of the observations}

The catalog of variability survey covers a total area of 1080 sq deg, 
these observations 
were obtained between 1998 and 2008 with the QUEST camera and 
the 1.0/1.5 m J\textasciidieresis{u}rgen Stock Schmidt telescope 
located at the 
Venezuelan National Astronomical Observatory, Llano del Hato,
M\'erida, Venezuela. The observations were obtained in drift-scan mode
in the celestial equator, for a more detailed description of the camera
and the drift-scanning technique see \citet{b14}. 

The catalog of variability survey was completed in previous work by
\citet{b6} and \citet{b15}. The reduction techniques are
essentially the same as those in \citet{b3}.


\subsection{Extinction}

We analyzed 2.5 sq deg of the catalog of variability survey. Data in this
region is affected by the spatially variable reddening (0.18 mag $\leq E(B-V)\leq$1.6 mag) 
at galactic latitude below $\sim$14.3 degree. The \citet{b16} 
dust maps were  
used to correct the V-, R- and I- photometric bands of this region by the 
galactic extinction $A_V, A_R$ and $A_I$.


